cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.GT, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with resource management in a network of wireless VR users communicating over cloud-based small cell networks. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The proposed algorithm is based on the machine learning framework of echo state networks (ESNs). 
3. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The VR resource allocation problem is formulated as a noncooperative game. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with optimizing the computational and spectrum resources in a system. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with VR users sending and receiving panoramic images and tracking data.
